Description: 1990 Korean made Westone Villain Graphite. Has the ORIGINAL modulus graphite neck with the 22 fret ebonal fretboard. 2 single EMG Select single coils, and an EMG Select humbucker in the bridge, complete with coil tap. Also has a Kahler Spyder trem bridge. Now the "project" part of the description. It needs the locking nuts and screws, an arm, the low E string fine tuner, (yes, there is a screw there that works perfectly in a pinch.) a strap pin on the bottom, and the Kahler needs to be set up. (If you play with Kahlers, you have all of those parts in a drawer somewhere. Or you can purchase them on eBay here.) As you see in the pics, the neck is great, with a tiny mark on the back of it, that won't show in the pics and you can't feel when you play, and the body has a few scraps, bumps and bruises. (I have no clue how that one grouping of marks happened. like some idiot dropped a screw driver on it many times.) And has the normal bumps and scrapes you would expect from a 28 year old shredder guitar. Has a non original Gigbag.
